title: Gamma radiations from the proton capture of 25Mg.

x4freetext: Gamma radiations from the proton capture of 25Mg.

x4codes.hlp: University of Kansas, Lawrence, KS, United States of America

x4freetext: Facility is not given.
The gamma rays produced by the reaction were
detected with a 12.7 cm*12.7 cm NaI crystal mounted on
a Dumont 6363 photomultiplier tube. A 7.5 cm thick
collimator was inserted between the target and the
detector. A 7.5 cm*7.5 cm NaI crystal was used as the
second detector in a slow-fast coincidence arrangement.
The targets were prepared by the evaporation of 25MgO
on to gold backings. This material was available with
an isotopic enrichment exceeding 95%. These targets
were mounted in a special target chamber that allowed
good thermal contact between the target backing and the
walls of the chamber to minimize heating by the beam.
The targets had a thickness of less than 2 keV.
